Scripts to fetch translations from bab.la, tyda.se
folkets lexikon and folkets synonymlexikon.

DESCRIPTION

The script svensk-engelsk.sh translates from Swedish
to English. There are also a number of symlinks that
calls the same script but translates from other from-to
language combinations that bab.la supports. To add a new
combination just create a new symlink.

Another script, tyda.sh, fetches translations from tyda.se.
The site tries to determine source language automatically
and translates from/to english/swedish.

The scripts folkets_lexikon_ensv.py, folkets_lexikon_sven.py
and folkets_syn.py fetch translations/synonyms from local
xml-files. Run the script update_folkets.sh to fetch the
xml-files before running the python scripts.

Finally babla.tcl is an Eggdrop script that calls the
other scripts when commands are given in the channel the
eggdrop bot is logged in to. The commands are:

!babla   - svensk-engelsk.sh
!tyda    - tyda.sh
!lexin   - folkets_lexikon_sven.py
!folkets - folkets_lexikon_sven.py
!folken  - folkets_lexikon_ensv.py
!folksyn - folkets_syn.py


REQUIREMENTS

The scripts call:
- html2text (https://github.com/aaronsw/html2text)
- perl
- python (2.5+ for xml parsing)


EXAMPLES

./svensk-engelsk.sh uppsats

This will try to get the translation of the word 'uppsats'.
If parsing is successful the output should look something like:

paper {substantiv}
essay {substantiv}
composition {substantiv}
article {substantiv}

While the command:

./engelsk-tysk.sh annotate

will translate the word 'annotate' from English to German (tyska).

Without a word

./svensk-engelsk.sh

will list all from-to combinations activated.
